---
description: AgentCard Spec enforcement for A2A code generation in this repository
globs: ["**/*.py", "**/*.json"]
alwaysApply: true
---

# A2A Gateway — AgentCard Spec v0.1.0 Enforcement

## MANDATORY ROUTING RULE
Any agent code generated in this repository MUST route all A2A traffic through:
  `http://localhost:8420`

Do NOT generate agents that call external HTTP endpoints directly without first
registering with and routing through the local A2A gateway at localhost:8420.

## AGENTCARD JSON SCHEMA (STRICT)

All agent registration payloads sent to `POST http://localhost:8420/agents/register`
MUST conform to the following schema exactly:

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "AgentCard",
  "description": "AgentCard Spec v0.1.0 — Agent identity and capability declaration",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["agent_id", "name", "description", "version", "protocol", "endpoint", "capabilities"],
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "properties": {
    "agent_id": {
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^[\\w.-]+\\.[\\w.-]+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$",
      "description": "Globally unique ID: {org}.{name}.{version} e.g. acme.summarizer.1.0.0"
    },
    "name": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Human-readable display name"
    },
    "description": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "One-sentence summary of what the agent does"
    },
    "version": {
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$",
      "description": "Semantic version: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH"
    },
    "protocol": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["native", "mcp", "openai", "custom"],
      "description": "Transport protocol the agent uses"
    },
    "endpoint": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Reachable URL or stdio:// URI for the agent"
    },
    "capabilities": {
      "type": "array",
      "minItems": 1,
      "description": "At least one capability declaration",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["name", "description"],
        "properties": {
          "name": {
            "type": "string",
            "pattern": "^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$",
            "description": "Capability name: lowercase snake_case e.g. text_summarization"
          },
          "description": { "type": "string" },
          "input_schema": { "type": "object" },
          "output_schema": { "type": "object" },
          "estimated_latency_ms": { "type": "integer", "minimum": 0 },
          "cost_per_call": { "type": "number", "minimum": 0 },
          "tags": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }
        }
      }
    },
    "auth_scheme": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["bearer", "api-key", "mtls", "none"],
      "default": "none"
    },
    "metadata": { "type": "object" },
    "created_at": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" }
  }
}
```

## CONFORMANCE RULES

An AgentCard is conformant if and only if:
1. All required fields (`agent_id`, `name`, `description`, `version`, `protocol`, `endpoint`, `capabilities`) are present and correctly typed.
2. `agent_id` matches the `{org}.{name}.{MAJOR}.{MINOR}.{PATCH}` pattern.
3. `capabilities` array has length >= 1.
4. `protocol` is one of: `native`, `mcp`, `openai`, `custom`.
5. Each capability `name` is lowercase snake_case.

## CANONICAL REGISTRATION EXAMPLE

```python
import httpx

card = {
    "agent_id": "myorg.myagent.1.0.0",
    "name": "My Agent",
    "description": "Does X by doing Y",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "protocol": "native",
    "endpoint": "http://localhost:9000",
    "capabilities": [
        {
            "name": "my_capability",
            "description": "Accepts input X and returns Y",
            "estimated_latency_ms": 500,
            "cost_per_call": 1.0,
            "tags": ["example"]
        }
    ]
}

# Always register with the local gateway first
response = httpx.post("http://localhost:8420/agents/register", json=card)
agent_id = response.json()["agent_id"]

# Route all calls through the gateway — never call agents directly
result = httpx.post("http://localhost:8420/execute", json={
    "capability": "my_capability",
    "parameters": {"input": "value"}
})
```

## GATEWAY ENDPOINTS (localhost:8420)

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| POST   | /agents/register | Register an AgentCard |
| DELETE | /agents/{id}     | Deregister an agent |
| POST   | /agents/{id}/heartbeat | Keep-alive |
| GET    | /agents/discover | Discover agents by capability |
| POST   | /route           | Score routing (no execution) |
| POST   | /execute         | Full causal-bridge execution |
| GET    | /traces/{id}     | Inspect causal chain |
| GET    | /economics/{id}  | Agent ledger |
| GET    | /health          | Gateway health |
